    "body": "My guess is that you are not importing `@nomiclabs/hardhat-waffle` in your config, or that you are using an outdated version of `ethereum-waffle`. Assuming you are using waffle at all.\r\n\r\nIf you are not using waffle, then this happens because `.to.equals` uses loose equality (i.e. it uses `==`), and `parseEther` returns a BigNumber object.\r\n\r\nPlease use our [discord server](https://hardhat.org/discord) if you have more questions.",
